snippet.textDisplay:
Interesting fact:

The bonus that players received for winning Super Bowl I in 1967 was $15,000, which adjusted for inflation is about $115,500 in today’s money.

The bonus today for winning the Super Bowl is $124,000.

Considering the revenue generated by the Super Bowl today compared to Super Bowl I, which didn’t even sell out, an equivalent raise of $8500 is a little head scratching.
